David
The hotel was $60. Gas+insurance came to $28 for my car, and $20 for Brian's car (his mom paid insurance). So here's what I have people down as still owing:

Travis: $60 hotel + $24 cars - $61 paid = $23
Ben: $60 hotel + $28 car - $25 paid = $63
Heather: $60 hotel + $28 car - $60 paid = $28
Brian: $60 hotel - $17 paid - $40 gas money I am collecting = $3
Jessie: $60 hotel + $4 banana boat = $64 (contact Brian for car)
Mike: $60 hotel + $20 ice house = $80 (contact Brian for car)
RJ: $60 hotel - $60 paid = $0
Teresa: $60 hotel + $20 car = $80 (you can pay either me or Joe)
Joe: $60 hotel + $24 cars - $640 hotel bill = -$556

Everything look right?

Brian
This does not look right. You subtracted $40 from what I owe you for gas, but then wrote contact Brian for car when in fact they should just pay David for my gas.
